---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Domarn Group | Case Study | Adam Barnes"
  description="Case study: government-grade document conversion for Domarn Group, producing clean HTML and Govspeak for GOV.UK, including work for the Department for Transport."
  canonical="https://www.adambarnes.biz/case-study-domarn-group.html"
  ogDescription="Government-grade document conversion for Domarn Group, producing clean HTML and Govspeak for GOV.UK, including work for the Department for Transport."
  ogImage="https://www.adambarnes.biz/assets/og-image.jpg"
  ogType="article"
  bodyClass="page-webdesign page-case-study"
  active="web-design"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "CreativeWork",
    "name": "Domarn Group — GOV.UK Document Conversion",
    "url": "https://domarncreative.co.uk",
    "creator": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Adam Barnes",
      "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "description": "Ongoing document conversion work for Domarn Group, transforming complex InDesign and Word documents into clean HTML and Govspeak for GOV.UK publication, including work for the Department for Transport.",
    "keywords": ["HTML", "Govspeak", "GOV.UK", "Accessibility", "Document Conversion", "Department for Transport"]
  }
  </script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/"},
      {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Web Design", "item": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/web-design.html"},
      {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Domarn Group", "item": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/case-study-domarn-group.html"}
    ]
  }
  </script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Domarn Group — Case Study",
    "description": "Case study: government-grade document conversion for Domarn Group — producing clean HTML and Govspeak for GOV.UK, including work for the Department for Transport.",
    "about": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Domarn Group",
        "url": "https://domarncreative.co.uk"
    },
    "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/case-study-domarn-group.html",
    "author": {
        "@type": "Person",
        "name": "Adam Barnes",
        "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "publisher": {
        "@type": "Person",
        "name": "Adam Barnes",
        "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "datePublished": "2026-04-01",
    "dateModified": "2026-04-22"
}
  </script>
  </Fragment>

<main>

    <!-- Page header -->
    <header class="section-header webdesign-header cs-header">
      <div class="cs-header-text">
        <h1 class="section-title">
          <span>Domarn</span>
          <span class="accent">Group</span>
          <span class="by-line">by Adam</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="section-intro">
          <span class="intro-lead">Government-grade content, delivered precisely.</span>
          Complex design documents transformed into clean, accessible HTML and Govspeak, ready for direct publication on GOV.UK with nothing left to fix.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-header-logo" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src="assets/logos/domarn-group.svg" alt="">
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Case study body -->
    <section class="cs-body reveal" aria-label="Case study detail">
      <div class="cs-body-inner">

        <!-- Meta strip -->
        <div class="cs-meta">
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Client</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value">Domarn Group</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Client site</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value"><a href="https://domarncreative.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">domarncreative.co.uk</a></span>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Services</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value">HTML · Govspeak · GOV.UK Publishing · Document Conversion · Accessibility</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Narrative -->
        <div class="cs-copy">
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The brief</h2>
            <p>Domarn Group is a London creative agency whose clients include some of the UK's most recognisable public sector organisations. The challenge is consistent: complex designed documents, policy papers, annual reports and consultation documents produced in Adobe InDesign and Microsoft Word, delivered as publication-ready content for GOV.UK.</p>
            <p>Not adapted. Not reformatted on arrival. Delivered correctly structured, fully accessible, and ready to go live without further processing by the publishing team.</p>
            <p>The output required two formats simultaneously: clean HTML formatted to the GOV.UK technical publishing standard, and Govspeak, the markdown dialect used by the government's content management system. Both meeting the UK government's accessibility requirements and content design patterns without exception.</p>

            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The work</h2>
            <p>Documents at this level carry real complexity. The source files contain nested tables, hierarchical headings, image assets, footnotes and structural formatting that carries meaning beyond its appearance on the page. Handling that accurately requires working with the document's underlying structure, not its surface.</p>
            <ul class="cs-list">
              <li>HTML and Govspeak produced as part of the same workflow</li>
              <li>Tables handled correctly: structured, labelled and accessible</li>
              <li>Images matched to their source positions with appropriate alt text</li>
              <li>Heading hierarchies and content structure preserved accurately</li>
              <li>Full compliance with GOV.UK accessibility and content design standards</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The output arrives ready for the publishing team to use. Nothing left to clean up, reformat or correct. The same care for clean, precise HTML runs through the <a href="case-study-adambarnes-biz.html">adambarnes.biz build</a>, applied to performance and AI search visibility.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The outcome</h2>
            <p>The Department for Transport has been the principal project through Domarn Group for three consecutive years. Each delivery has met their specification exactly, confirmed by the team on every round.</p>
            <p>Government publishing operates to tight timelines and exacting standards. A document that arrives incorrectly structured, inaccessibly formatted, or requiring further processing is a problem. One that arrives ready to publish is not.</p>
            <p>What previously required weeks of manual processing and recoding is now delivered complete. The work continues as new documents come through.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Workflow infographic -->
    <section class="flow-infographic" aria-label="Document conversion workflow">
      <p class="flow-caption">The conversion workflow</p>
      <div class="flow-diagram" id="flow-diagram">

        <div class="flow-node" id="fn1">
          <div class="flow-node-num">01</div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">Source Document</div>
          <div class="flow-node-body">
            <div class="source-badges">
              <div class="app-badge app-badge--id">Id</div>
              <div class="app-badge app-badge--word">W</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-node-sub">InDesign · Word</div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-arrow-col">
          <div class="flow-arrow-label">Export</div>
          <div class="flow-arrow-track" id="fa1"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-node" id="fn2">
          <div class="flow-node-num">02</div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">Raw HTML</div>
          <div class="flow-node-body">
            <pre class="flow-code flow-code--messy">&lt;span <span class="noise">style="color:
#231f20;font-family:
'Minion-Bold';
font-size:10pt"</span>&gt;
  Policy...
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p <span class="noise">style="margin:0pt;
padding:0pt;
text-indent:0"</span>&gt;</pre>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-node-sub">Unstructured output</div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-arrow-col">
          <div class="flow-arrow-label">Convert</div>
          <div class="flow-arrow-track" id="fa2"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-node flow-node--output" id="fn3">
          <div class="flow-node-num">03</div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">Clean Output</div>
          <div class="flow-node-body">
            <div class="flow-split">
              <div>
                <div class="flow-split-tag">Clean HTML</div>
                <pre class="flow-code flow-code--clean">&lt;h2&gt;Policy&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Structured,
accessible.&lt;/p&gt;</pre>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flow-split-tag">Govspeak</div>
                <pre class="flow-code flow-code--govspeak">## Policy

Structured,
accessible.</pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-node-sub">Two formats · one workflow</div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-arrow-col">
          <div class="flow-arrow-label">Publish</div>
          <div class="flow-arrow-track" id="fa3"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-node flow-node--govuk" id="fn4">
          <div class="flow-node-num">04</div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">Published</div>
          <div class="flow-node-body">
            <div class="govuk-inner">
              <svg class="govuk-crown-svg" viewBox="0 0 132 97" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
                <path d="M66 0L52 25 32 10l10 40H90L100 10 80 25 66 0zM20 55h92v10H20z"/>
                <rect x="15" y="68" width="102" height="29" rx="2"/>
              </svg>
              <div class="govuk-wordmark">GOV.UK</div>
              <div class="govuk-ready">Ready to publish.<br>Nothing left to fix.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-node-sub">Dept. for Transport</div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Back link + CTA -->
    <div class="cs-footer-nav reveal">
      <a href="web-design.html" class="cs-back-link">← Back to Web Design</a>
      <a href="contact.html" class="btn">Start a project</a>
    </div>

  </main>
</Base>
